look at you list                                                                       print ls
make dir                                                                               mkdir /root/fir create a dir
create a file                                                                          touch /root/fir/filename
veiw the content of the file                                                           cat /root/fir/filename
use Vim editor to edit file                                                            vim /root/fir/filename
insert mode in vim                                                                     i
Then you can write something what you want to in your file
You can add anything in it.
After it you can look foer the  designated content what you want to.
If you want to store your content.Firstly,you should exit the insert mode. 
If you want to store and exit your content.                                            :wq
If you would like to  just only store your content.                                    :w
